column2: Extract Twitter feed attributes and store them in DynamoDB
must be a valid IP CIDR range of the form x.x.x.x/x.
must be the name of an existing EC2 KeyPair.

{u'Fn::Base64': {u'Fn::Join': [u'', [u'#!/bin/bash -xe 
', u'exec > >(tee /var/log/user-data.log|logger -t user-data ) 2>&1 
', u'echo BEGIN ', u"date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'
", u'# Install the files and packages from the metadata
', u'/opt/aws/bin/cfn-init -v ', u'         --stack ', {u'Ref': u'AWS::StackName'}, u'         --resource TwitterEC2Instance ', u'         --region ', {u'Ref': u'AWS::Region'}, u'
', u'sudo su root 
', u'mkdir -p /home/ec2-user/rekognition-workshop 
', u'chmod -R 777 /home/ec2-user/rekognition-workshop
', u'yum -y update 
', u'pip install twitter 
', u'pip install textblob 
', u'pip install boto3 
', u'# Signal the status from cfn-init
', u'/opt/aws/bin/cfn-signal -e $? ', u'         --stack ', {u'Ref': u'AWS::StackName'}, u'         --resource TwitterEC2Instance ', u'         --region ', {u'Ref': u'AWS::Region'}, u'
', u'echo END ', u"date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'
"]]}}
